        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 7:17PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 716 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Chico, or 9 miles northwest of Bridgeport, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Chico and Lake Bridgeport around 720 PM CDT.
Alvord around 730 PM CDT.
Sunset around 735 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Vineyard, Wizard
Wells, Cundiff, Greenwood, Mallard, Fruitland, Park Springs, Runaway
Bay, Lake Bridgeport, and Montague.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
